    "updated_at": "2015-06-24T16:46:59Z",
    "body": "This one is interesting. When the option is set on the browser window the following function is called in native_window_views.cc. Because the window is not yet visible the second part of the IsVisible check is called. The following API call does not appear to work on Windows.\n\n``` cpp\nwindow_->native_widget_private()->ShowWithWindowState(ui::SHOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN);\n```\n\nFull function:\n\n``` cpp\nvoid NativeWindowViews::SetFullScreen(bool fullscreen) {\n  if (IsVisible())\n    window_->SetFullscreen(fullscreen);\n  else\n    window_->native_widget_private()->ShowWithWindowState(\n        ui::SHOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN);\n#if defined(OS_WIN)\n  // There is no native fullscreen state on Windows.\n  if (fullscreen)\n    NotifyWindowEnterFullScreen();\n  else\n    NotifyWindowLeaveFullScreen();\n#endif\n}\n```\n\nI found that if I commented out the IsVisible check and just allowed it to set fullscreen then it worked as expected.\n\n``` cpp\nvoid NativeWindowViews::SetFullScreen(bool fullscreen) {\n  //if (IsVisible())\n  window_->SetFullscreen(fullscreen);\n  //else\n  //  window_->native_widget_private()->ShowWithWindowState(\n  //      ui::SHOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN);\n#if defined(OS_WIN)\n  // There is no native fullscreen state on Windows.\n  if (fullscreen)\n    NotifyWindowEnterFullScreen();\n  else\n    NotifyWindowLeaveFullScreen();\n#endif\n}\n```\n\nSo that said I guess our princess is in the following castle:\n\n``` cpp\n// Do we need to call this? If so, need to figure out why it's currently broken.\nwindow_->native_widget_private()->ShowWithWindowState(ui::SHOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN);\n```\n"
  },
